<HEADLINE>
CHINA BELIES PROMISES FOR MORE PRESS FREEDOM: GOVERNMENT
SPOKESMAN
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, March 3 (CNA) 03/04/07  00:03:04 (By Maubo Chang)
</P>
<P>
China has belied its promise for more press freedom by denying
the Hong Kong- based Apple Daily the right to cover the annual
conference of the National People's Congress and the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference which are going on in
Beijing,  Minister for Government Information  Office Cheng Wen-
tsang said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Cheng said Beijing authorities has denied the Apple Daily access
to cover the meetings of the two above organizations despite of
its promises in January to ease restrictions on foreign
correspondents's coverage of Chinese affairs in the leadup to
2007 Beijing Olympics.
</P>
<P>
He urged the international  community to prod the Chinese
authorities to fulfill its promises to respect freedom of press
and expression.
</P>
